### Command 1: `/ds-sync-tokens`

Write to `.claude/commands/ds-sync-tokens.md`:

```markdown
---
description: Sync design tokens from Figma to [detected token file path]
argument-hint: [figma-url] [--dry-run]
allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Agent]
---

# Sync Design Tokens from Figma

## Arguments
$ARGUMENTS — parse: Figma URL (required), `--dry-run` (preview changes without writing)

## Steps

1. Spawn `figma-extractor` to pull all variables from the Figma file
2. Read the current token file at `[detected token file path]`
3. Diff: which tokens are new, changed, or removed?
4. If `--dry-run`: print the diff and stop
5. If not dry-run: apply changes to `[detected token file path]`
   - New tokens → append
   - Changed values → update in place
   - Removed tokens → comment out with `/* REMOVED: [date] */` — never silently delete
6. Report: N added, N changed, N flagged for removal

## Token Collections to Sync
[List actual collection names from Figma extraction — e.g. Primitives, Color, Spacing, Typography]

## Rules
- Never hardcode hex values — always write as CSS custom properties or TS constants
- Preserve all existing comments and custom properties not in Figma
- Flag any token in code that no longer exists in Figma instead of auto-deleting
```

