### Command 3: `/ds-audit`

Write to `.claude/commands/ds-audit.md`:

```markdown
---
description: Scan the codebase for hardcoded design values that should be design tokens
argument-hint: [--fix] [--path <directory>]
allowed-tools: [Read, Glob, Grep, Write, Edit, Bash]
---

# Design System Audit

## Arguments
$ARGUMENTS — parse: `--fix` (auto-replace found values with tokens), `--path` (scope to a directory)

## What to Scan

### Hardcoded colors
Search for hex values, rgb(), hsl() in component and style files:
```bash
grep -rn "#[0-9a-fA-F]\{3,6\}\|rgb(\|hsl(" [scan path] \
  --include="*.css" --include="*.scss" --include="*.tsx" --include="*.vue" \
  --exclude-dir=node_modules
```

### Hardcoded spacing
Search for pixel values in CSS that should be token references:
```bash
grep -rn "padding:\s*[0-9]\|margin:\s*[0-9]\|gap:\s*[0-9]" [scan path] \
  --include="*.css" --include="*.scss" --exclude-dir=node_modules
```

### Hardcoded font values
```bash
grep -rn "font-size:\s*[0-9]\|font-family:\s*['\"]" [scan path] \
  --include="*.css" --include="*.scss" --exclude-dir=node_modules
```

## Output Format
```
DS AUDIT REPORT
===============
Hardcoded colors:    N occurrences in X files
Hardcoded spacing:   N occurrences in X files
Hardcoded fonts:     N occurrences in X files

Top offenders:
  [file path]:[line] → [value] → suggested token: [token name]
  ...

Total violations: N
```

## If `--fix`
For each violation: replace the hardcoded value with the closest matching token from `[detected token file]`.
If no token match exists within 10% tolerance → flag as `NEEDS_TOKEN: [value]` and skip.
Write a `DS_AUDIT_FIX_LOG.md` listing every change made.

## Known Token File
[detected token file path] — [N tokens loaded]
```

